<div class=Section1>

<h3 align=center style='text-align:center'>Verification of Logic Operations</h3>

<h3 style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>The first verification unit we will construct will be for the logical
operations.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>We will only make use of one
component from the Open Verification Library, assert_implication.<span
style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>Read its description from the documentation (<a
href="../../../Reference/ovl_docs/html/assert_implication.html">Assert_Implication</a>).
<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<h3 style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>We will use a comparison of ALUop as the antecedent expression; this
identifies which operation we are verifying. A comparison of the returned
result ( R ) to the expected result (For the case of ALUop =”0000” we expect a
result of <i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>A AND B</i> ) is used as the
consequent expression.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>If the antecedent
expression is true but the consequent expression evaluates false, an error will
be reported to the simulator.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>We have
the option of writing what that error message will be and its severity level
(Right Click on Component </span><span style='font-family:Wingdings;mso-ascii-font-family:
"Times New Roman";mso-hansi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-char-type:symbol;
mso-symbol-font-family:Wingdings;font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span
style='mso-char-type:symbol;mso-symbol-font-family:Wingdings'>à</span></span><span
style='font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'> Object Properties </span><span
style='font-family:Wingdings;mso-ascii-font-family:"Times New Roman";
mso-hansi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-char-type:symbol;mso-symbol-font-family:
Wingdings;font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span style='mso-char-type:
symbol;mso-symbol-font-family:Wingdings'>à</span></span><span style='font-weight:
normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'> Generics).<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> 
</span>Use severity_lvl = ERROR, any level higher than this will cause the
simulator to halt operation when errors are detected.<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<h3 style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-weight:normal;mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h3>

<h3 align=center style='text-align:center'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
